🌊WE CAME, WE SAW, WE CONQUERED 🌊
As water season finally comes to a close, NDUC left it all in the water at Club Crew World Championships 2024! 🏅✨ Swipe to get a better look at these WORLD CHAMPIONS🏆
A massive thank you to our coaches, teammates, and everyone who cheered us on from the shore, you made this season one to remember ❤️🙌This journey was more than just the medals—it was about pushing past our limits, lifting each other, and making EVERY STROKE COUNT💥
Another huge shoutout to @lb.limitbreaker for making us look and feel like champions in our brand new Vikings and Valkyries jerseys!
We’re stepping off the water, but the fire keeps burning. Here’s to the off-season, the hard work ahead, and the legacy we’re building together! 💪🔥

📣 Hey New College! Lockers are now available for rent and will be assigned on a first-come, first-serve basis. 📣

The lockers are half-sized and located in the basements of Wilson Hall (40 Willcocks St) and Wetmore Hall (300 Huron St). The rental form is available in our bio! :)
Introducing Dr. Kumar! 🎉 Join us on September 20th, from 4:00-6:30 PM at the Medical Science Building, room 3153, to learn more about his impactful research in the field of neuropsychiatry. 🧠

Introducing the first annual collaboration between the Psychology Students’ Association and the Neuroscience Association for Undergraduate Students! 🎉🧠

The Neuropsychiatry Symposium highlights ground breaking research in both neuroscience and psychology. Hear about the most current research in both fields from a distinguished panel of primary investigators!

Join us on Friday, September 20th from 4:00-6:30 pm to learn more about research you can get involved in! 💡

📣📣 STUDENT (and community members) RALLY GROUP DETAILS FOR GRASSY NARROWS RIVER RUN

Meet in front of the UTSU building (Huron entrance) at 11:15AM this WEDNESDAY. We will march together to Grange Park in solidarity with Grassy Narrow’s 2024 River Run! ✊🌍

Bring your protest signs, friends, and water bottles!
(If you don’t have a sign, no worries! We will have some extra)

First more information on why you should come, visit @grassy.narrows.solidarity and freegrassy.net

Excited to see you there!! 🐟✊💧🎣🌅🌿🌱
